  "conclusion": "The L8 c2 selected-projection/native-state/batch-GEMV-output native-full hidden gate turns green when the pre-QKV boundary (input RMSNorm, QKV prep, and scratch) and context/gate are forced per-row. The narrower context+gate+O split remains token-green but hidden-red, while pre-QKV+context stays hidden/token green even with the existing batch-GEMV O path and batch post-attention/MoE/copy path. This eliminates the need to force O/MoE/post-attention for this controlled hidden gate and pins the remaining native-full blocker to the coupled pre-QKV plus context/gate setup. Defaults were not changed and no throughput/scaling claim is made.",
